cs.DL, cs.CR, cs.OS, cs.IR, cs.DC 

This paper is primarily focused on digital preservation, which falls under the category of cs.DL (Digital Libraries). The paper also discusses the use of open source software and peer-to-peer technology, which could potentially fall under cs.OS (Operating Systems). The LOCKSS system is designed to preserve access to academic journals, which could be considered a form of information retrieval, placing it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the system involves security measures to protect against tampering or unauthorized access, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
